postcontent: auser C96 “Bolo” Broomhandle PistolM1921 Made Famous by the BolsheviksHere we present a Mauser C-96 Broomhandle Pistol, made circa 1923-1930. The Mauser Construktion 96 was the Mauser Company’s most successful pistol and was even used by the likes of Winston Churchill during the Boer Wars. He is attributed as saying that it was “the best thing in the world”.This particular variant has a shorter barrel and is also known as the M1921 or the “Bolo”, the latter due to its association with the Bolsheviks and the Red Army after the Bolshevik Revolution. “Bolo” was a derogatory term for those who identified as Bolsheviks. The victorious communists purchased many of these pistols and likely scavenged them from their defeated enemies, the Whites, who also bought them in large quantities. These were certainly popular in other parts of the world as well and were heavily adopted by many in the post-WWI German Freikorps, who fought against communists in the Balkans.This specimen is in very good overall condition. 50% of the original blue finish remains. title: For Sale/Trade:  Ultra-Super Beater Stevens 320
postcontent: This shotgun is a little rough around the edges but it still works fine and I have video to prove it if you would like to see it run fast. It is a Stevens 320 and was imported by Savage Arms. It holds 5 in the tubular magazine then one in the chamber. The Stevens 320 is very similar to the Winchester 1300. I would know as I have taken apart both firearms before. This particular shotgun had jettisoned its own bead sight from the gun while shooting slugs so you are just left with a threaded hole near the muzzle. I am not sure what the choke is on the barrel but it appears to be cylinder choke, also the barrel 18.5 inches long. The receiver has provisions to accept a picatinny rail and I could throw one in for a little extra. In my expeirence this gun has done good with wax slugs, Remington, Federal, Winchester bird shot loads and Winchester slug loads but it chokes on Suprema Buckshot and Hornady Buckshot(half of the time). What I mean by this is that sometimes it has a harder time than usual extracting and ejecting spent shells but it was never something I couldn't handle by getting aggresive with the pump. Most times this gun will open up the action a little when shot if you dont have a hand on the forend. Which isn't really a problem, but you should just be aware of this. So if you want simple, cheap shotgun you can abuse and not worry about damaging then this is your gun.I will probably be in Des Moines around November 18th-20th so I could meet up there if you wish.Feel free to contact me any time at REDACTED. Texting may be more convenient for me.
